reviews.review: I thought this movie was great, there are nit picks, certainly not a perfect movie but considering it is carrying the weight of 40 plus years of lore and that this is technically the 11th block buster style movie in the franchise it's incredible that we even made it here. the last movie is a fun roller coaster of emotions  that had me gasping several times out loud, it cranked up the stakes to 11 and just kept it there and when the heros and protaganist finish the fight I felt like I could finally breath again. I think as a whole the trilogy really made me fall in love with the main characters, Rey, Fin, Poe, Ben, and I am just happy to see how everything turned out. In the end I  felt like C3P0 who really enjoyed watching their friends one last time on the big screen. To everyone who worked on this movie thank you, if this trilogy was anything, it certainly wasn't easy.
Excellent from start to finish. It's an amazing finish to a journey I started with "A New Hope"!
It did not live up to the hipe. It was an ok movie. Hope they do better with the next one.  There was more they could have done with this movie.

Too much in one movie, too long.  Sad to see end of an era that began 40 years ago. Ridley and Driver were excellent but plot was convoluted and walked too many Last of the Jedi  revelations. Wish they had not used Fisher footage. She wasn't needed in the story and how she died was just plain dumb.

Wow, out like a turd. Maybe this movie is hoping for a participation award like the message it's trying to convey? Or maybe it's not trying to convey? I don't know because the story was so remarkably full of fluffy sap and chasms at the same time, it's hard to tell. Maybe that's the award they were going for? I guess anybody can come back from the dead now if you really hope and believe hard enough... And so many cereal box nuggets of truth to quote.
Too much of the same fight over and over

Fun movie, but flawed in many ways... A little too much going on for its own good, Just like Force Awakens, it's a really safe and fan service type movie that takes the Star Wars movies in no new direction and creates a stale rehash, just like all the other poor remakes Hollywood it bringing back these days.
All stories were tied up nicely.
